<div id="main_content">
	<h2>Virtual Game Teaches Navy Recruits Life-and-Death Skills</h2>
	
	<p class="article_info">
		
			By Rebecca Basu
		
		<span class="date">June 16, 2011</span></p>
	
	
	
		<div class="article_img" style="width: 345px;">

			<img alt="Article Main Picture" src="../resources/sites/UCF/content/live/NEWS/2000/NE2579/en_US/DamageMain.jpg" height="226" width="345"  /> 
			
				<p class="photo_credit">Photo: Courtesy Office of Naval Research</p>
			
			<p>U.S. Navy recruits at the Recruit Training Command in Great Lakes, Ill., play "Damage Control Trainer," a computer game that helps them learn operational skills relating to flood and fire control and preventing casualties aboard ship. </p>
			
				<p class="note"><a class="full_photo" id="popup.jsp?article_id=002400416a60cde7013003bb6e240049fc">Full Photo</a></p>
			
			
			
			
					
						
						
						
					
			
			
			
					
						
						
						
					
			
			
			
		</div>
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
		
